===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally written {{och-l|戹|yoke}} and later {{och-l|*厄}}.

Afterwards {{och-l|*車|carriage}} was added to differentiate, forming {{Han compound|車|厄|ls=ic|ls2=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=carriage|t2=yoke|nocap=y}}.

===Etymology===
Probably from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*ʔik||to strangle}}, whence also {{och-l|縊|to strangle}}.

